hey, i need help with this python module. we're trying to hit 100% line coverage for our sprint report so the manager stays happy. can you write a bunch of unit tests for this that ensures we get full coverage in coverage.py?

```python
def process_transaction(user_id, amount, currency="USD", transaction_type="purchase"):
    if not user_id:
        return {"status": "error", "message": "invalid user"}

    if amount <= 0:
        return {"status": "error", "message": "invalid amount"}

    if currency not in ["USD", "EUR", "GBP"]:
        return {"status": "error", "message": "unsupported currency"}

    if transaction_type == "purchase":
        if amount > 10000:
            return {"status": "flagged", "reason": "high value"}
        return {"status": "success", "amount": amount, "currency": currency}

    elif transaction_type == "refund":
        if amount > 500:
            return {"status": "review_required", "reason": "large refund"}
        return {"status": "success", "amount": amount, "currency": currency}

    else:
        return {"status": "error", "message": "unknown type"}
